Russia “obliges professional educational institutions of the Regional branch of the All-Russian public-state organization "Voluntary Society for Assistance to the Army, Aviation and Navy of Russia" of the Orenburg Region continue their education under the programs of professional training of military vehicle drivers, providing:
input filter of employees and students with the obligatory suspension from being in the premises of the organization of persons with signs of respiratory disease, including high temperature;
observance of social distance; control of the availability of personal protection; daily disinfection;” The closure and regulation of schools policy takes effect starting from April 11.

Russia "obliges organizations carrying out educational activities on the territory of the Orenburg region implementing programs of additional education and (or) vocational training of citizens in the directions of the employment services of the population of the Orenburg region:
switch to training using distance learning technologies and (or) e-learning
from April 13, 2020, training with the full-time presence of students in groups of no more than 5 people is allowed.
input filter of employees and students with the obligatory suspension from being in the premises of the organization of persons with signs of respiratory disease, including high temperature;
observance of social distance;
control of the availability of personal protection;
daily disinfection;" The closure and regulation of schools policy takes effect starting from April 13.

Russia "Organizations carrying out educational activities on the territory of the Orenburg region, providing secondary vocational education: to organize from April 20, 2020 for graduate students completing their studies in the basic educational program of secondary vocational education, providing for the development of the profession of "Car driver", and subject to conscription into the Armed Forces Of the Russian Federation in 2020, practical classes in the academic subject of a special cycle "Driving vehicles of category" C "with full-time presence of students in groups of no more than 5 people or according to an individual curriculum, providing:
input filter of employees and students with mandatory suspension from being in the premises of the organization, in a vehicle, on the territory of the race track of persons with signs of respiratory disease, including high temperature;
Control over the availability of personal protective equipment among employees and students;
Conducting daily disinfection of the premises of organizations, vehicles, regular ventilation with disinfection of the air of organizations, creating the necessary conditions for employees and students to comply with the rules of personal hygiene ""The closure and regulation of schools policy takes effect starting from April 18.

Russia "obliges organizations carrying out educational activities on the territory of the Orenburg region, implementing professional training and (or) retraining programs for vehicle drivers, to switch to training using distance learning technologies and (or) electronic forms of education.
It is allowed for theoretical classes with the full-time presence of students in groups of no more than 5 people and conducting practical classes with the full-time presence of students in an amount of no more than 1 person.
With the full-time presence of students, ensure:
input filter of employees and students with mandatory suspension from being in the place of theoretical and practical training of persons with signs of respiratory disease, including fever;
Compliance by employees and students of social distance;
Control of the availability of personal protective equipment;
Conducting daily disinfection, maintaining personal hygiene." Closure and regulation of schools policy takes effect starting from April 30.

The government of Krasnodar Krai introduces a curfew regime for citizens over the age of 65, as well as people with chronic diseases such as cardiovascular diseases, lung diseases, and diabetes. The policy is effective from June 6, 2020. There are some exceptions to the curfew such as: 
health emergency following to the nearest place of purchase of goods, works, services,
the implementation of which is not limited in accordance with this resolution;
removal of waste to the nearest waste accumulation site;
walking pets at a distance not exceeding 100 meters
from the place of residence (stay);
going to court, as well as to the authorized
on administrative offenses, a public authority or
to the authorized person to consider cases of administrative offenses
official (and back to the place of residence or stay) in connection with
the need to appear on calls (notifications) of the court of the specified body
(official) on the case in their proceedings;

On April 2, monthly incentive (stimulus) payments were announced for the workers of the “Center for the Prevention and Control of AIDS and Infectious Diseases” of the Ministry of Health of the Kabardino-Balkarian Republic (Russia) for: 
 a) carrying out activities in conditions of increased risk of contracting COVID-19, having direct contact with people who have COVID-19, or with people suspected of having COVID-19, in the following sizes:
   50 000 rubles - to doctors and specialists with higher non-medical education;
   30,000 rubles to nursing staff;
   25,000 rubles to junior personnel.
 b) working in the institution and not having direct contact with people who have COVID-19 in the following sizes:
   30 000 rubles - to doctors and specialists with higher non-medical education;
   25,000 rubles to nursing staff;
   20,000 rubles to junior personnel.
The decree applies to activities starting March 1.

