Starting from March 30, citizens of Ingushetia (Russia) are prohibited from leaving their place of residence (stay) except for 
a) cases of seeking emergency medical care and other direct threats to life and health; 
b) cases of moving to (and from) the place of their business and work that has not been suspended; 
c) the implementation of activities related to movement within the territory of the Republic of Ingushetia, if such movement is directly related to the implementation of activities that have not been suspended (including the provision of transportation and delivery services), as well as going to the nearest place of purchase of goods, works, services, the implementation of which has not been suspended;  
d) walking pets at a distance not exceeding 100 meters from the place of residence (stay), removal of waste to the nearest place of accumulation of waste. 
Restrictions established by this policy do not apply to cases of medical care, activities of law enforcement, civil defense and emergency situations authorities and their subordinate organizations, bodies on supervision in the field of consumer protection and human well-being, and other bodies whose actions are directly aimed at protecting life, health and other rights and freedoms of citizens, including crime counteraction and policing.

On March 30, the Karachay-Cherkessia Republic (Russia) is put under lockdown. The citizens are to shelter in place unless  
getting urgent medical care or experiencing direct threats to life and health; 
going to work that is not restricted; 
going to the nearest places of purchase of food, supplies and services that are not restricted; 
walking pets (no further than 100 metres away from home); 
taking out the trash.

Russia, Arkhangelsk district, March 30: citizens are ordered not to leave their place of residence (lockdown), except in the following cases:
- seeking emergency medical care and cases of other direct threats to life and health;
- following to the place (from the place) of the implementation of the activity (work), which is not suspended in accordance with the previously adopted acts;
- following to the nearest place of purchase of goods, works, services, taking out garbage and walking pets at a distance not exceeding 100 meters from the place of residence.

On March 31 until April 6, the Stavropol Krai (Russia) is put under lockdown. The citizens are to shelter in place unless 
getting urgent medical care or experiencing direct threats to life and health; 
going to work that is not restricted; 
travelling for work purposes that are not restricted; 
going to the nearest places of purchase of food, supplies and services that are not restricted; 
walking pets (no further than 100 metres away from home); 
taking out the trash.

On March 31, Alexander Uss the governor of Krasnoyarskiy region signed a decree "On the restriction of citizens visiting public places (self-isolation) in the Krasnoyarsk Territory". 

The Krasnoyarsk Territory, along with other regions of the country, is moving into self-isolation until the sanitary and epidemiological situation improves.

It is allowed to leave the apartment and the house only:
- to move from place to place for activities (including work), which are not suspended;
- for seeking emergency medical help;
- to make purchases at the nearest working store or pharmacy;
- for walking with pets within a radius of 100 meters from the house;
- for garbage removal;
- in other emergency cases.

On March 31, the Kabardino-Balkaria Republic (Russia) is put under lockdown. The citizens are to shelter in place unless 
getting urgent medical care or experiencing direct threats to life and health;
going to work that is not restricted; 
going to the nearest places of purchase of food, supplies and services that are not restricted;
walking pets (no further than 100 metres away from home); 
taking out the trash.

From April 18, lockdown with following conditions is imposed in Republic of Mordovia (Russia): citizens must not leave their place of residence (stay), except for the following cases:
1) requests for emergency (urgent) medical care and cases of other direct threats to life and health;
2) following to the place (from the place) of carrying out activities (work), performing official duties in an organization that is not suspended in accordance with the decree of the President of the Russian Federation of April 2, 2020 No. 239.
3) visiting the nearest place of purchase of goods and services, the sale of which is not restricted;
4) visits to the court, notary, lawyer, military enlistment office, bodies of inquiry and investigation, and other law enforcement agencies;
5) delivery of minors to and from a pre-school educational organization;
6) visits to a medical or veterinary organization;
7) visits to credit institutions and post offices;
8) delivery of medicine, food and basic necessities to disabled relatives, providing them with assistance;
9) delivery of medicine, food and essential goods by volunteers to certain categories of citizens with a passport and a personal card (badge) of the volunteer;
10) walking pets at a distance not exceeding 100 meters from the place of residence (stay);
11) waste removal to the nearest waste storage area.

Lockdown with following conditions is imposed in Kamchatka krai (Russia) from May 11 to May 31. Citizens are not allowed to leave
place of residence (stay), with the exception of 
1) following to the place (from the place) of activity (including work) that is not suspended,
2) carrying out activities (including work) that are not suspended,
3) requests for emergency (urgent) medical care and other direct threats to life and health; 
4) following to the nearest place of purchase of goods and services, the sale (provision) of which is not suspended; 
5) walking pets at a distance not exceeding 100 meters from the place of residence (stay); 
6) waste removal to the nearest waste storage site; 
7) physical education and outdoor sports provided that no more than 2 people are engaged in joint activities and the distance between the participants is not less than 5 meters;
8) walking on the street no more than 2 people together, subject to social distancing, excluding visiting places of mass stay of people, including playgrounds.

Russia "obliges Local governments of municipalities of the Orenburg region:
organize control over the observance of the isolation regime by persons:
citizens of the Russian Federation, foreign citizens, stateless persons who arrived on the territory of the Orenburg region from foreign states or other subjects of the Russian Federation;
Persons living together with persons in respect of whom the decisions of the chief state sanitary doctor in the Orenburg region on isolation were adopted;
Persons over 65;
All persons living in the Orenburg region;" The new task force, bureau or administrative configuration policy takes effect starting from March 31.

Russia "obliges the Ministry of Social Development of the Orenburg Region, within its competence:
organize work with social service organizations with round-the-clock stay of people, regardless of the form of ownership, including socially oriented non-profit organizations that provide social services to ensure the isolation of social service organizations, providing for the shift nature of the work of employees of these organizations;
Interact with social service organizations to fulfill the requirements and recommendations provided for by this decree." The other type policy takes effect starting from April 30.

On April 25, the government of Stavropol Krai (Russia) recommended all organizations operating in the region to inform their employees:
   on the clinical signs of COVID-19;
   about action plan in case of detecting signs of COVID-19 in an employee and (or) members of their family;
   about action plan in case of detecting signs of COVID-19 in an employee at the workplace;
   on the prevention of COVID-19, on the rules of personal and public hygiene: the regimen of regular handwashing with soap or skin antiseptics during the whole working day, after each visit to the toilet, before each meal;
   about the undesirability of travelling to regions and countries with registered cases of COVID-19;
   on the rules for the use of workwear and PPE, including masks and gloves;
   about hotlines to call a doctor and to get the necessary advice about COVID-19;
   about administrative responsibility for spread of misinformation.

On April 25, the government of Stavropol Krai (Russia) has ruled that all organizations performing vehicle maintenance and repair should be informing their employees: 
on the clinical signs of COVID-19; 
about action plan in case of detecting signs of COVID-19 in an employee and (or) members of their family; 
about action plan in case of detecting signs of COVID-19 in an employee at the workplace;
on the prevention of COVID-19, on the rules of personal and public hygiene: the regimen of regular handwashing with soap or skin antiseptics during the whole working day, after each visit to the toilet, before each meal;
about the undesirability of travelling to regions and countries with registered cases of COVID-19; 
on the rules for the use of workwear and PPE, including masks and gloves; 
about hotlines to call a doctor and to get the necessary advice about COVID-19.

April 3, government of Kamchatka krai (Russia) requires heads of fisheries, mining and construction organizations seeking to recruit seasonal (rotational) job workers from other subjects of the Russian Federation and foreign labor, upon arrival of seasonal (shift) workers:
a) to carry out a meeting of workers in places of arrival, transportation to places of residence with the provision of isolation from other employees and the population of Kamchatka krai for a period of 14 calendar days;
b) take measures to minimize contacts of the arrived workers with the population of the Kamchatka territory;
C) if it is not possible to transport employees to their place of work on the day of arrival on the territory of the Kamchatka territory, place them in temporary accommodation facilities. For temporary accommodation, it is allowed to use recreation centers, sanatoriums and hotels located outside of cities Petropavlovsk-Kamchatsky and Yelizovo;
d) when employees have the first respiratory symptoms, ensure that they are immediately isolated and seek medical help without visiting a medical organization.

From April 11, head of Mordovia Republic (Russia) requires that citizens who arrive from the subjects of the Russian Federation where cases of new coronavirus infection (COVID-19) are registered:
1) to transmit information about the place and dates of their stay, return, contact information to the relevant local government body at the place of residence (place of stay);
2) to self-isolate at home at the place of residence (place of stay) for a period of 14 days from the date of return to the Republic of Mordovia, do not leave the place of residence (place of stay), except for cases of applying for emergency (urgent) medical care and cases of other direct threats to life and health, purchasing food, medicines, disinfectants, personal protective equipment, walking pets at a distance not exceeding 100 meters from the place of residence (stay), waste removal to the nearest place of waste accumulation;
3) when the first signs of respiratory infection appear, stay at the place of residence and immediately seek medical help from a medical organization at the place of attachment without visiting medical organizations (calling a doctor at home) to issue disability certificates;
4) comply with the instructions of Officials of the Federal service for supervision of consumer rights protection and human welfare in the Republic of Mordovia to conduct additional sanitary and anti-epidemic (preventive) measures related to the observance of self-isolation at home.

It is recommended to the heads of organizations and individual entrepreneurs operating in the territory of the Republic of Mordovia (Russia) starting from March 18, 2020: 
1) to cancel business trips to foreign countries and within Russian Federation, except for urgent business trips; to recommend employees to refrain from all trips to republics and subjects of the Russian Federation with an unfavorable situation associated with the spread of the COVID-19, unless they are caused by extreme necessity; 
2) provide body temperature measurement to employees in the workplace with mandatory suspension from the workplace of persons with elevated temperature; 
3) assist employees in ensuring compliance with the self-isolation regime at home; 
4) send information to the Office of the Federal service for supervision of consumer rights protection and human welfare in the Republic of Mordovia on cases of suspension from the workplace of persons with elevated body temperature; 
5) upon a request from the Office of the Federal service for supervision of consumer rights protection and human welfare in the Republic of Mordovia, immediately provide information about all contacts of a person who has a new coronavirus infection COVID-2019 in connection with the performance of their work functions; 
6) ensure daily wet cleaning of rooms with the use of disinfectants; 
7) install bactericidal irradiators in places where people stay in closed rooms.

Russia, Penza region: From March 28, 2020 to April 5, 2020, the following activities are suspended:
- retail markets and fairs selling non-food products;
- shopping centers for the sale of non-food group of goods, with the exception of children's stores, essential goods and pharmacies.

Russia, Penza region: From March 28, 2020 to April 5, 2020, the following activities are suspended:
- retail markets and fairs selling non-food products;
- shopping centers for the sale of non-food group of goods, with the exception of children's stores, essential goods and pharmacies.

In Russia, the Magadan government requires businesses to limit the number of people who can simultaneously be in the same place starting from March 31
–Up to 50 square meters - no more than 5 people;
- up to 100 sq. m - no more than 10 people;
- up to 200 sq. m - no more than 25 people;
- over 200 sq. m - no more than 50 people. "

Russia " obliges physical culture and sports organizations: to suspend activities until further notice;
to carry out sports training exclusively using distance technologies;
exclude the direction of workers and persons undergoing sports training outside the municipalities of the Orenburg region;
Do not allow persons engaged in and undergoing sports training, including from other subjects of the Russian Federation, in the organization of sports training until further notice." The restriction and regulation of businesses policy takes effect starting from April 4.

