In Russia, starting from April 23 the Magadan government shuts down all businesses that are related to 
"activities of astrologers and mediums;
- social services such as escort services, dating bureaus, and marriage agencies;
- services for the care of pets, such as maintenance and training;
- activities of genealogical organizations;
- activities of tattoo and piercing parlors;
- services of shoe shiners, doormen, valet parking, etc .;
- activities related to the operation of personal service machines

On April 25, the government of Stavropol Krai (Russia) recommended all organizations operating in the region:
    to shift to work from home all workers for whom it's possible, especially persons from risk groups (over 65 years of age, with chronic diseases, reduced immunity, pregnant women);
    carry out contactless deliveries;
    shift to electronic interactions and document exchange;
    not to hold any mass events;
    restrict business trips.
During their technological process:
    restrict contact between teams of workers via separate offices, rooms, workshops;
    provide respiratory protection and gloves to workers responsible for movement of materials, products and documents between separated entities;
    restrict movement of employees on the territory of the organization unrelated to their work;
    industrial enterprises have to ensure functioning ventilation system, minimize contact of workers with industrial aerosols, vapours, gases;
    not to exceed the following guidelines: up to 50 sq. meters - no more than 5 people; up to 100 sq. meters - no more than 10 people; up to 200 sq. meters - no more than 25 people; over 200 sq. meters - no more than 50 people;
    use special markings to ensure social distancing (min 1.5 m);
    daily thermometry and health monitoring;
    daily cleaning with disinfectants;
    air disinfection and regular airing of rooms;
    provide PPE to workers and control its use.

Starting April 25 in Stavropol Krai (Russia), the following recommendations are offered for organizations that provide dry cleaning and laundry services:
   cleaning with disinfectants;
   monitoring workers' temperature and health;
   only admit necessary personnel and customers;
   limiting contact between personnel and customers: make appointments mandatory;
   ensure social distancing by special marking at least 1.5 m apart;
   air disinfection; staff using PPE (masks and gloves); 
   airing of premises every 2 hours;
   wet cleaning of premises after each client;
   temporary suspension from work of persons from risk groups (over 65 years of age, with chronic diseases, reduced immunity, pregnant women).

Starting April 25 in Stavropol Krai (Russia), the following recommendations are offered for organizations carrying out vehicle maintenance:
   cleaning with disinfectants; 
   monitoring workers' temperature and health;
   install antiseptic dispensers;
   only admit necessary personnel and customers;
   limiting contact between personnel and customers: make appointments mandatory;
   ensure social distancing by special marking at least 1.5 m apart;
   air disinfection;
   staff using PPE (masks and gloves);
   airing of premises every 2 hours or after each visitor.
   temporary suspension from work of persons from risk groups (over 65 years of age, with chronic diseases, reduced immunity, pregnant women).

Starting April 25 in Stavropol Krai (Russia), the following recommendations are offered for hair and beauty salons:
   require weekly negative COVID-19 test from all staff;
   notify local municipal governments about lists of workers who have negative tests;
   immediately remove workers with positive COVID-19 tests from the workplace;
    cleaning with disinfectants;
    monitoring workers' temperature and health daily; 
    only admit necessary personnel and customers;
    limiting contact between personnel and customers: make appointments mandatory;
    ensure social distancing outdoors in case of a queue;
    provide services to each visitor in a separate office;
    organize shift work for employees
    ensure social distancing by special marking at least 1.5 m apart;
    air disinfection;
    staff using PPE type IV - pajamas, a medical gown, a cap, a mask (disposable or reusable) or a respirator, gloves, socks, slippers or shoes;
    daily cleaning;
    airing of premises every 2 hours; 
    wet cleaning of premises after each client;
    instrument disinfection after each client; 
    temporary suspension from work of persons from risk groups (over 65 years of age, with chronic diseases, reduced immunity, pregnant women).

In Khakassiya, In accordance with the Decree of the President of Russia, the week of 28 March-5 April is declared non-working. This provision does not apply to employees of:

- medical institutions and pharmacies;

- organizations providing the population with food and essential goods;

- organizations performing urgent work in emergency situations;

- organizations carrying out urgent repair and loading and unloading operations.

Russia obliges "Employers operating on the territory of the Orenburg region, using a rotational work method, in relation to employees who arrived on the territory of the Orenburg region from other subjects of the Russian Federation:
ensure the minimum number of arrived workers involved in the production process; 
Organize transport delivery of arrived workers to the place of employment and back.
Upon arrival of these workers, ensure that they are tested for coronavirus infection and be isolated until negative coronavirus test results are obtained. In the absence of the possibility of testing for the presence of coronavirus infection, exclude contacts of the arrived workers with the local population;
Determine the place of residence of the arrived workers, limiting their presence outside the territory in which they perform labor activities;
Notify local authorities about the arrival of workers from other subjects of the Russian Federation and agree on the placement of the arrived workers, excluding contacts with the local population.
Ensure filling out questionnaires indicating the place of stay and contact phone numbers
Ensure enhanced control over the health of the arrived workers, minimizing their contacts with other employees of the organization;
Do not allow arriving workers with signs of respiratory illness to enter the workplace." The restriction and regulation of businesses takes effect starting from April 30.

The Government of the Rostov Region establishes that during non-working holidays, weekends and non-working days from May 1 to May 11, 2020, inclusive permits and certificates issued to citizens for movement are valid solely for the purpose of carrying out following activities: state and municipal institutions and enterprises;
backbone organizations;
continuously operating organizations; medical organizations
organizations performing urgent work in an emergency and (or) when there is a threat of the spread of a disease that poses a danger to others, in other cases, endangering the life, health or normal living conditions of the population;

Russia "obliges to suspend from March 28 to July 5, 2020 on the territory of the Orenburg region the work of: catering organizations and individual entrepreneurs providing catering services, with the exception of:
organizations providing catering services, for the delivery of finished products, serving take-away without visiting the premises of these organizations by citizens;
Organizations providing catering services, servicing employees of enterprises, institutions of organizations." The restriction and regulation of businesses policy takes effect starting from June 19.

Russia "obliges the Ministry of Health of the Orenburg Region to suspend, from April 6, 2020, until further notice, licensing, if necessary, to conduct field inspections in relation to license applicants and licensees who have submitted applications for license renewal, of the following activities:
medical activity of medical organizations;
pharmaceutical activity;
activities on the circulation of narcotic drugs, psychotropic substances and their precursors, the cultivation of narcotic plants.Restriction and regulation of government services takes effect starting from April 6."

